1
00:28:26,047 --> 00:28:28,357
You've done very well so far, Fedorin.
到目前为止你做得非常好，Fedorin

2
00:28:28,647 --> 00:28:30,957
It's nothing more than blackmail.
只是勒索而已，没什么

3
00:28:31,027 --> 00:28:34,044
Blackmail? I have threatened you with nothing.
勒索？我没拿任何事情威胁你

4
00:28:34,207 --> 00:28:36,198
No, but you would if I refused.
是没有，但如果我决绝的话你就会

5
00:28:36,367 --> 00:28:38,756
Fedorin, I keep on telling you,
Fedorin，我一再告诉你

6
00:28:38,927 --> 00:28:43,762
this is just a form of comprehensive insurance, hm?
这只是某种形式上的综合保险，嗯？

7
00:28:43,927 --> 00:28:46,441
There's nothing for you to worry about.
你没有什么可担心的

8
00:28:46,607 --> 00:28:50,998
My dear man, I've done nothing
but praise you ever since we first met.
我亲爱的伙计，自从我们初次见面，我对你就只有赞叹

9
00:28:51,167 --> 00:28:55,638
I said you should be European Controller.
I said I would support you.
我说过你将是欧洲控制员，我说过我会支持你

10
00:28:55,807 --> 00:28:58,641
You've found out things about me,
lies that would damage me.
你发现了我一些事情，一些会毁我的谎言

11
00:28:58,707 --> 00:29:00,925
On the contrary, I am doing you a good turn.
恰恰相反，我正在做对你有利的事情

12
00:29:00,707 --> 00:29:03,625
I am actually suppressing facts about you.
事实上我是在压制你那些事实

13
00:29:03,687 --> 00:29:08,045
- Lies, I tell you!
- Lies... Truth... Who knows?
- 谎言，我跟你说！  - 谎言...真实...谁知道呢

14
00:29:08,147 --> 00:29:12,405
But we wouldn't like to put him to the test, would we?
但我们并不喜欢拿他做测试，对不？

15
00:29:18,487 --> 00:29:20,478
There.
给你

16
00:29:21,447 --> 00:29:23,438
What's this?
这是什么？

17
00:29:23,607 --> 00:29:28,681
Used in the right way, at the right time,
it can dictate your own future
用对了方法，用对了时间，它就能决定你自己的未来

18
00:29:28,847 --> 00:29:31,725
and the future of Alexander Denes.
还有 Alexander Denes 的未来

19
00:29:31,887 --> 00:29:33,525
Poison...
毒药...

20
00:29:33,687 --> 00:29:34,298
I want you to take a message... 
我要你带一个消息...

21
00:29:34,565 --> 00:29:39,998
- McCrimmon! What are you doing dressed like this?
- Leader's orders.
- McCrimmon! 你穿成这样是要做什么？  - 领袖的命令

22
00:29:40,087 --> 00:29:42,698
Now that you're here, I've got some questions to ask you.
既然你在这里，我有些问题要问你

23
00:29:42,807 --> 00:29:44,456
I have better things to do, thank you.
我有重要的事情要做，谢谢你

24
00:29:44,527 --> 00:29:47,137
I want to know what Salamander and Giles Kent were discussing
我想要知道 Salamander 和 Giles Kent 在讨论什么

25
00:29:47,227 --> 00:29:50,037
- when I saw you last time?
- It's not for me to tell you that.
- 就我上次见到你的时候 - 这个不该我来告诉你

26
00:29:50,107 --> 00:29:51,956
I am concerned of Salamander's safety.
我担心 Salamander 的安全

27
00:29:52,007 --> 00:29:53,556
Giles Kent is Salamander's bitter enemy.
Giles Kent 是 Salamander 的死敌

28
00:29:53,627 --> 00:29:57,756
If Salamander wishes you to know that,
I dare say he'll tell you himself.
如果 Salamander 想让你知道，我敢说他会自己告诉你的

29
00:29:57,853 --> 00:29:59,732
You'll get no confidential items out of me.
你从我这里得不到机密信息

30
00:30:00,547 --> 00:30:03,652
Listen. You must go away from here.
听着。你必须离开这里

31
00:30:03,747 --> 00:30:05,582
Don't get caught up in Salamander's world.
别搅和到 Salamander 的世界里面

32
00:30:05,747 --> 00:30:08,940
Why? What do you mean? You sound as if you don't like him.
为什么？你什么意思？听起来你好像不喜欢他

33
00:30:09,057 --> 00:30:11,106
- Like him? I ...
- Hello there.
- 喜欢他？我  - 你好啊

34
00:30:11,267 --> 00:30:13,542
Finish writing those menus.
把那些菜单写完

35
00:30:16,427 --> 00:30:18,083
- Did you hear that?
- Aye. Work on her. 
- 你听到了吗？  -  嗯，做她的工作

36
00:30:18,164 --> 00:30:20,156
I have a feeling she can tell us something about Salamander. 
我感觉她能告诉我们一些 Salamander 的事情

37
00:30:20,247 --> 00:30:21,901
All right. As soon as I can. What have you been doing?
好吧，我尽快。你在做些什么？

38
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:23,856
I managed to slip out and tell Astrid everything that's happened.
我找机会溜了出去，跟 Astrid 讲了这里所发生的事情

39
00:30:23,967 --> 00:30:26,403
- You might have told me, Jamie!
- There wasn't time.
- 你该告诉我的!  - 没有时间

40
00:30:26,507 --> 00:30:28,200
- She's trying to get Denes away.
- And take him to the Doctor?
- 她在竭力带走 Denes   - 带他去见博士？

41
00:30:28,300 --> 00:30:30,400
- He'd believe Denes.
- Aye, he would.
- 他会相信 Denes 的.   - 是，他会的

42
00:30:30,567 --> 00:30:32,927
How can she get in? Salamander's got guards are everywhere.
那她怎么进来？到处都 Salamander 的警卫

43
00:30:33,087 --> 00:30:36,199
She's got friends here. They're going to arrange passes and the right sort of uniform.
她在这里有朋友。他们会准备通行证和合适的制服

44
00:30:36,367 --> 00:30:39,518
- What sort of uniform?
- I don't know. Messenger delivery or something. Ssh!
- 什么样的制服？  - 我不知道，通讯人员什么的吧。嘘!

45
00:30:40,887 --> 00:30:46,917
I don't know whether Fedorin is to be regarded as a new Controller or not.
我不知道 Fedorin 是否会被推选为(fixme)新的控制员

46
00:30:47,087 --> 00:30:50,079
The burden of office is heavy, my friend.
公务担子很重，我的朋友

47
00:30:50,807 --> 00:30:52,240
They've gone.
他们走了

48
00:30:52,407 --> 00:30:56,036
Astrid and Giles Kent were right.
Salamander IS an evil man.
Astrid 和 Giles Kent 是对的。Salamander 的确是邪恶的人

49
00:30:56,207 --> 00:30:59,995
- I can sense it from all the people here.
- He's bad, all right.
- 我能从这里所有人中感觉到  - 他是坏人，好吧

50
00:31:00,167 --> 00:31:03,921
He's had Denes arrested,
and has Fedorin eating out of his hand.
他把 Denes 抓了，让 Fedorin fixme

51
00:31:04,087 --> 00:31:07,841
- Why do that?
- Replace an honest man with a weaker man,
- 怎么会这样?  - 将一个诚实的人换成一个懦弱的人

52
00:31:08,007 --> 00:31:11,682
but somehow have a hold on him,
and take over the territory.
然后想法抓住他的把柄，就可以夺走版图了

53
00:31:11,847 --> 00:31:15,681
I see - when everything's in a turmoil
because of the earthquakes.
我明白了 - 因为地震，一切都混乱了

54
00:31:15,847 --> 00:31:17,963
And that's lucky to say the least.
说起来这还是幸运的

55
00:31:18,807 --> 00:31:24,837
But you don't really believe that Salamander
could cause earthquakes, do you?
但你不是真的相信 Salamander 能制造地震吧，信吗？

56
00:31:40,787 --> 00:31:43,180
I'm certain Salamander's behind this.
我肯定 Salamander 是幕后黑手

57
00:31:43,287 --> 00:31:46,180
Jamie and Victoria will tell you how bad he is.
Jamie 和 Victoria 会告诉你他有多坏

58
00:31:46,347 --> 00:31:48,065
But why make earthquakes?
但为什么制造地震呢？

59
00:31:48,227 --> 00:31:53,460
Years ago, if a country wanted to invade another,
it threw that country into confusion,
多年以前，如果一个国家打算入侵另外一个，就会让它陷入混乱

60
00:31:53,627 --> 00:31:57,506
making it weak and ripe for take-over.
That's happening here.
削弱它，等机会吞并。这里也是这种情况

61
00:31:57,667 --> 00:32:03,378
You're saying Salamander has found a way
to harness the natural forces of the Earth.
你是说 Salamander 找到了一种方法来利用地球的自然力量

62
00:32:03,547 --> 00:32:08,496
That's difficult to accept.
I'm not saying it's impossible, mind you.
这很难让人接受。但我不是说这是不可能的，注意

63
00:32:09,947 --> 00:32:15,385
You say it's coming from the research station.
Salamander's research station, eh?
你说这来自研究站，Salamander 的研究站，嗯？

64
00:32:15,547 --> 00:32:18,300
That's what I believe, in spite of... Ssh!
我相信是这个，尽管...嘘！

65
00:32:21,467 --> 00:32:24,300
In spite of the fact he invented the sun-store
尽管他发明了日光存储器

66
00:32:24,467 --> 00:32:27,903
and directed conserved energy to areas starved of sun.
把存储的能量转到了日光匮乏的地区

67
00:32:28,067 --> 00:32:31,423
- What made you suspicious?
- The money he was spending.
- 什么让你尝试了怀疑？  - 他花的钱

68
00:32:31,587 --> 00:32:35,660
The materials and food.
It didn't match the requisition orders.
材料和食物。与合理订单的数量不符

69
00:32:35,827 --> 00:32:39,103
- That's valuable evidence.
- New orders appeared.
- 这证据很有价值  - 有新订单出现了

70
00:32:39,267 --> 00:32:42,896
I was made out to be the criminal -
by suggestion, of course.
而我就被安排成了犯罪分子 fixme

71
00:32:43,887 --> 00:32:46,438
I couldn't do it, Salamander. I couldn't do it.
我干不了，Salamander，我干不了这事

72
00:32:46,607 --> 00:32:49,519
I stood there with this man's life in my hands.
我站在那里，手里攥着这个人的性命

73
00:32:49,687 --> 00:32:52,121
This powder - I couldn't use it.
这药粉 - 我下不了手

74
00:32:52,287 --> 00:32:55,757
I gave you the chance
to become something. Somebody.
我给了你机会让你成就点什么，成为一个人物

75
00:32:55,927 --> 00:32:59,158
- You failed to take it.
- There must be some other way.
- 但你没能接住   - 肯定有其它的方法

76
00:33:00,367 --> 00:33:04,201
Of course, my friend. Don't worry.
当然，我的朋友。别担心

77
00:33:04,367 --> 00:33:06,278
- What?  - Don't worry.
- 什么？  - 别担心

78
00:33:06,447 --> 00:33:08,440
You try, you fail - so what?
你努力了，然后失败了 - 那又怎样？

79
00:33:08,547 --> 00:33:10,440
The moon doesn't fall out of the sky!
月亮又不会跑到天外面去！

80
00:33:10,607 --> 00:33:13,724
Come and sit down. Have a drink, huh?
过来坐下。喝一小杯，哈？

81
00:33:14,687 --> 00:33:18,043
Cheer up. We'll find another way.
振作起来。我们想别的办法

82
00:33:18,207 --> 00:33:19,879
I really did try.
我真的尽力试过了

83
00:33:20,047 --> 00:33:21,560
Of course you did.
当然

84
00:33:21,727 --> 00:33:23,319
Don't worry.
别担心

85
00:33:23,487 --> 00:33:25,557
Forget it, huh?
忘了它，哈？

86
00:33:25,727 --> 00:33:28,321
I have an alternative.
我有另一个方法

87
00:33:29,447 --> 00:33:30,880
Your health.
你的健康

88
00:33:32,447 --> 00:33:37,760
I hope you will appreciate this wine.
It's made for me especially in Alaska.
我期望你喜欢这杯酒。这是在 Alaska 特意为我酿造的

89
00:33:47,927 --> 00:33:50,202
One chance, my friend.
只有一次机会，我的朋友

90
00:33:50,367 --> 00:33:52,517
I said one chance!
我说过只有一次机会！

91
00:33:52,687 --> 00:33:56,123
The new man says he's seen someone
in the kitchen gardens.
那个新人说他在厨房花园看见了什么人

92
00:33:56,287 --> 00:33:59,203
Very well. Oh, see to that, will you?
那好。哦，盯着点，行吗？

93
00:33:59,407 --> 00:34:02,203
Suicide, of course. Such a pity.
自杀，当然是。好可惜

94
00:34:04,247 --> 00:34:07,444
- I can't see anything.
- Over there by the trees!
- 我看不到任何东西  - 在那边的树丛里！

95
00:34:07,607 --> 00:34:09,786
He's armed, too. Get down!
他也有枪，趴下！

96
00:34:09,807 --> 00:34:11,486
I'm going out there. Stay down here.
我去那边。蹲在这里

97
00:34:11,647 --> 00:34:15,242
When the rest of the guards come,
send them after me.
其它警卫过来后，让他们跟我来

98
00:34:21,207 --> 00:34:23,163
Astrid's going to get you away.
Astrid 会把你弄走 fixme

99
00:34:23,327 --> 00:34:27,036
An attempt has been made to rescue this man.
Take him to the car.
有人试图救这个人。带他去车里

100
00:34:28,287 --> 00:34:29,686
I'm sorry, Janos.
抱歉，Janos

101
00:34:29,847 --> 00:34:31,280
Stop!
站住！

102
00:34:32,047 --> 00:34:35,084
After them! Arrest that girl!
去追他们！逮捕那个女孩儿！

103
00:34:35,247 --> 00:34:37,920
Well, we all seem to be here,
好了，看来我们都在这里了

104
00:34:38,087 --> 00:34:41,318
except the third member of your escape committee.
除了你那逃跑小队的第三个成员

105
00:34:41,487 --> 00:34:45,480
- What are you talking about?
- You were seen with a girl in the park.
- 你在说什么？  - 有人看见你和一个女孩儿在园区

106
00:34:45,647 --> 00:34:50,357
- The one who tried to escape with Denes.
- We don't even know her.
- 那个女孩儿打算同 Denes 一同逃跑  - 我们都不认识她

107
00:34:51,027 --> 00:34:52,506
A diversion was caused.
fixme

108
00:34:52,667 --> 00:34:57,616
- There was no one outside the kitchen.
- There was, and there was shooting.
- 厨房外面没有谁  - 有，还有人开枪

109
00:34:57,787 --> 00:35:01,826
Three shots have been fired from this gun.
It's yours, isn't it?
这把枪开过三枪。这是你的，对吧？

110
00:35:01,987 --> 00:35:04,865
Pretending to save my life was ingenious,
假装救我的命，这很高明啊

111
00:35:05,027 --> 00:35:09,464
but ingenuity requires a constant stream of new ideas.
但高明就需要后面一系列的新点子

112
00:35:09,627 --> 00:35:12,505
Yours seem to have dried up.
而你似乎已经枯竭了

113
00:35:14,187 --> 00:35:19,056
I come to the Central Zone.
An attempt is made on my life.
我到了中央区，有人试图要我的命fixme

114
00:35:19,227 --> 00:35:21,616
Denes proves to be a traitor.
Denes 到头来是一个叛徒

115
00:35:21,787 --> 00:35:24,859
Fedorin commits suicide because I uncover him.
Fedorin 自杀了，因为我揭露了他

116
00:35:25,027 --> 00:35:28,463
Do your job, Bruce.
You can see they're all in this.
干你的活吧，Bruce。你可以看到他们都在这里面

117
00:35:29,627 --> 00:35:31,857
All right. Take them away.
好吧。把他们带走

118
00:35:32,027 --> 00:35:34,336
Take your hands off me!
把你的手拿开！

119
00:35:34,507 --> 00:35:36,941
I think you should tell me what's going on.
我想你会告诉我这都是怎么回事

120
00:35:37,107 --> 00:35:39,826
One minute you're working with McCrimmon...
前一分钟你与 McCrimmon 挺好

121
00:35:39,987 --> 00:35:44,936
- I thought he saved my life.
- I mean before that. In Kent's office.
- 那是我以为他救了我的命  - 我是说之前，在 Kent 的办公室

122
00:35:47,587 --> 00:35:49,224
- What are you talking about?
- 你在说些什么？

123
00:35:49,487 --> 00:35:52,341
- I saw you there.
- I haven't seen Kent in months.
- 我在那里见到你了  - 我都好几个月没有见过 Kent 了

124
00:35:52,487 --> 00:35:55,941
You were with him, Fariah and the youngsters.
你跟他在一起，还有 Fariah 和这几个年轻人 

125
00:35:56,107 --> 00:35:59,622
I thought it was so curious,
I spoke to Benik about it.
我就觉得很奇怪，还同 Benik 谈过此事

126
00:35:59,787 --> 00:36:03,939
- That's the reason I came to this zone.
- But I tell you...
- 这就是我来这个区的原因  - 但我告诉你

127
00:36:04,107 --> 00:36:07,782
I must get back to the research centre.
You will come with me.
我必须回到研究中心去。你得跟我来

128
00:36:07,947 --> 00:36:09,938
It was you.
那就是你

129
00:36:11,387 --> 00:36:15,175
Or someone like you.
或者某个很像你的人

